Review Title: Best time best place to eat
Review Text: Guys have eaten at Asian Kitchen many many times everytime food excellant service excellant. I have got to knoe the owners and staff very well and all my meals are the best. Menu has anything you want Vietnamese food, vegetarian and many many western dishes. I am in Viet Nam for 45 dsys will eat 75% ofvmy meals there. For me quality of food always the same excellant. Great location good people best food. And for you penny pinchers always get your moneys worth never walk away hungry. Also good selection of cold beers, wine and mixed drinks.

Cuisine excellente et pas chère !!
Cocktails pareil !! 
Je recommande dans ce quartier très animé, piéton et populaire 👌

Food was amazing and we had a few cold beers. My first time trying crocodile satay and it was so good. We enjoyed vegetarian spring rolls and had Squid sweet and sour, husband had Pad Thai and that was very good as well.

Review Title: Used to love it, will never go back there again (unfortunately quality has halved at best)
Review Text: On previous visits to Vietnam, this was a go to place because of the extensive menu catering to most requirements and pretty cheap cost. It was always great value for money and was quality food. So this visit we made our way here…Unfortunately, either of the owners have changed or their desire has changed because the food was greasy, smaller quantities and generally not enjoyable. Unfortunately I will not go here again.

Review Text:
a great experience
I had a wonderful trip to Ho Chi Minh City and enjoyed the cuisine here. It was a surprise to experience great food at Bep A restaurant.
The restaurant is located in a small alley near the hotel. Cheap prices, beautiful decoration and quite delicious.

This is a Vietnamese gem that can be found in an alley way.

I usually order similar dishes when going to different restaurants to see their take on the dish.

This is by far the best Vietnamese restaurant that I have been to here in Vietnam. They serve food which is fit to be found in a resort situation.

We ordered the bun thit nuong, char siu with egg and fried rice, ca phe sua da, tra da and mango smoothie.

The char siu was juicy unlike the usual type that you would get at other Asian restaurants. The mango smoothie was definitely fresh with small pieces of sweet mango that added to its rich texture.

The man at the front was so friendly and always had a smile on his face when dealing with customers.

If you are visiting Vietnam, then this is a restaurant that you should not miss!

Мы нашили этот ресторан в топ лучших, но были разочарованы. Пхо подают без лайма и зелени, зато кладут имбирь, который перебивает любой вкус и сверху плавает ПЕНКА! Мясо не вареное, а ошпаренное, жесткое и опять же даже пенку не собрали. Если будете здесь попробуйте жаренные спринг ролы, Пхо едите в соседнем заведении))

Review Text: We found this restaurant down an alley near our hotel, these alleyways are full,of lovely little restaurants serving good food at very reasonable prices. Most, like this one, are family run and you receive a warm welcome and they want to create a good impression. We have bee here a few times and food and service are excellent. The prices are very reasonable and we will be going back again! Highly recommended.

Review Text: Delicious food, great prices for food and drinks, very welcoming staff, will come back here again. Worth visiting the side streets off of Bui Vien for better deals and better atmosphere.
